ations in the redshift range\n$30\\leq z \\leq 100$ with a 0.01-MHz bandwidth and sub-arcminute angular\nresolution could potentially improve bounds by several orders of magnitude for\nmost features compared to current Planck bounds. At the same time, 21 cm\ntomography also opens up a unique window into features that are located on very\nsmall scales.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 May 2016 19:44:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 17 Aug 2016 14:41:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-28"}
