 a `kick'\norientation. While ejecta mass cannot be the only factor that determines the\nvelocity of supernovae compact remnants, we suggest it is a significant\ncontributor and that the ejecta based `kick' should replace the\nMaxwell-Boltzmann velocity distribution currently used in many population\nsynthesis codes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 31 May 2016 08:54:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-06-01"}
