onent of the current density in the direction of\nthe applied field. The presented numerical method is very promising for 3D\nmodeling of superconducting samples and power applications.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 31 May 2016 12:58:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 31 Oct 2016 16:32:55 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 7 Feb 2019 13:02:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-23"}
